  "prompt": "Do witches fly on brooms in front of the full moon at night?",
  "response": "The image of witches flying on brooms, especially in front of a full moon, is a popular trope in folklore, literature, and pop culture. This imagery often represents the idea of witches as mystical and powerful figures capable of supernatural feats. However, in reality, witches\u2014whether historical figures or modern practitioners of Wicca and other neopagan religions\u2014do not fly on brooms. The association largely comes from myths, stories, and artistic representations that have emerged over centuries. \n\nThe symbolism of the broom itself is sometimes linked to domesticity, fertility, and the idea of \"sweeping away\" negativity. So while the image of witches flying on brooms at night is a captivating one, it remains firmly in the realm of fiction and symbolism rather than reality.",
